ately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret was born in 1310, in England, United Kingdom. She married Robert de Ferrers 3rd Lord Ferrers of Chartley before 20 October 1330, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1331, in her hometown."},"et":{"1310–Aft 1331":"1310–pärast 1331","1309–1350":"1309–1350","1331–1367":"1331–1367","1310–1331":"1310–1331","before 20 October 1330":"enne 20. oktoobrit 1330","1367":"1367","Aft 1331":"pärast 1331","1310":"1310","1331":"1331","10 August 1331":"10. august 1331","1350":"1350","1309":"1309","Chartley Holme, Staffordshire, England":"Chartley Holme, Staffordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1310–Aft 1331":"1310–1331 jälkeen","1309–1350":"1309–1350","1331–1367":"1331–1367","1310–1331":"1310–1331","before 20 October 1330":"ennen vuotta 20. lokakuuta 1330","1367":"1367","Aft 1331":"1331 jälkeen","1310":"1310","1331":"1331","10 August 1331":"10. elokuuta 1331","1350":"1350","1309":"1309","Chartley Holme, Staffords